                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1073" type="given" value="TIMOTHY"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430612-1901-offence-1 t18430612-name-1073"></join>Timothy Maber</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430612-name-1074" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1074" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1074" type="surname" value="HAYWARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1074" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN HAYWARD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the employ of Timothy Maber, a wine-merchant at Islington. The prisoner was formerly in his service—about nine o'clock, on the 5th of June, I went into the back-yard and saw the prisoner in the act of taking these bottles off the premises in a crate—I let him go outside—I followed—he ran away when I called stop thief; but was stopped—this is my master's crate.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HORRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> You told him to bring them back? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, I asked what he was going to do? he said he was not going to take them away—I never said that he said he was going to take, them away—I desired him to take them in again—he did so, and put them down in the yard—I knew he lived at Bagnige Wells.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430612-name-1075" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1075" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1075" type="surname" value="KELLY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1075" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN KELLY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable N</hi> 360.) I took the prisoner running down Edward-street, towards Thornhill-bridge.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Was he running in a direction towards Btgnige Wells-road? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HORRY</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">called</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430612-name-1076" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1076" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1076" type="surname" value="ALLANSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1076" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY ALLANSON</persName>
                  </hi>. My husband is employed at a warehouse. I live in Wild-street—I have known the prisoner ever since he was ten years old—when he is a little excited he would not know what he was about—when he was very young his father struck him on the head.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430612-name-1077" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1077" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1077" type="surname" value="GARDNER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1077" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD GARDNER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a glass and bottle dealer, in Great William-street. The prisoner was in my service five years—he used frequently to com<lb></lb>plain of his head.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430612-name-1078" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1078" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1078" type="surname" value="SHUDMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1078" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>SARAH SHUDMAN</persName>
                  </hi>. My husband is a carman, and lives at Kennington. The prisoner is my brother—his head is very bad; he frequently complains that he is out of his mind, and fancies he is mad—when he has taken a drop of strong liquor he is half frantic, and does not know what he is doing.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430612-name-1079" type="witnessName">
